    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Landing Page Seriousness",
      "position": {
        "x": -300,
        "y": 0
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Landing Page Seriousness\n\nThe public root graph is now strong enough that it needs to become an intentional front door rather than a useful demo. This task graph defines the questions and decisions needed to reshape it.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": true,
        "root": true
      },
      "color": "#1976d2",
      "ports": [
        {
          "id": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "direction": "input",
          "dataType": "flow",
          "position": {
            "side": "left",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "direction": "output",
          "dataType": "content",
          "position": {
            "side": "right",
            "offset": 0.5
          }
        }
      ],
      "inputs": [
        {
          "key": "in",
          "label": "In",
          "type": "flow"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "key": "out",
          "label": "Out",
          "type": "content"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-entry",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Clear Entry Path",
      "position": {
        "x": 260,
        "y": -180
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 210,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Clear Entry Path\n\nWhat should a first-time visitor do first?\n\nThe landing graph needs one dominant journey instead of several equally plausible ones.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-identity",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Clear Identity",
      "position": {
        "x": 680,
        "y": -180
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 210,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Clear Identity\n\nThe public root and its linked graphs need intentional names, titles, and descriptions. `Untitled Graph` and `Untitled Project` weaken the front door immediately.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-hierarchy",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Stronger Hierarchy",
      "position": {
        "x": 260,
        "y": 80
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Stronger Hierarchy\n\nThe root graph currently mixes onboarding, philosophy, tasks, library links, and author notes. The landing page needs a clearer ordering of importance.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-signals",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Fewer Accidental Signals",
      "position": {
        "x": 680,
        "y": 80
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Fewer Accidental Signals\n\nDuplicate entries, old titles, and uneven naming make the site feel more experimental than it now deserves. The landing graph should reduce those accidental signals.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-conversion",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Intentional Conversion",
      "position": {
        "x": 1100,
        "y": 80
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Intentional Conversion\n\nDecide what a visitor should become after landing:\n- reader\n- explorer\n- builder\n- contributor\n- customer\n\nWithout this, the landing graph will stay broad instead of sharp.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-sequence",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Suggested Sequence",
      "position": {
        "x": 260,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Suggested Sequence\n\nA likely first pass for the root graph:\n\n1. What Twilite Is\n2. Why Graphs\n3. Try It\n4. Explore Library\n5. See The Task Graphs\n\nThis is a proposed visitor journey, not a final decision.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-questions",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Questions To Answer",
      "position": {
        "x": 740,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Questions To Answer\n\n- What is the primary visitor journey?\n- What should be above the fold in graph terms?\n- What gets demoted: author note, tasks, library, ontology, docs?\n- What are the exact naming fixes needed?\n- What visual/structural assets should be exported for external design tools like Canva?",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "landing-seriousness-output",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Design Export Goal",
      "position": {
        "x": 1220,
        "y": 360
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Design Export Goal\n\nOnce these questions are answered, the landing graph should be structured enough to export into a more polished design process or external tool without losing the graph-native reasoning behind it.",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false
      }
    },
